cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.NI 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method that integrates model pruning with federated learning to improve the efficiency of model training on edge devices. Other likely categories include "cs.DC" (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as federated learning involves distributed model training, "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as deep neural networks are commonly used in computer vision tasks, "cs.SY" (Systems and Control) as the proposed method involves optimizing the system performance by reducing computation, communication, and storage costs, and "cs.NI" (Networking and Internet Architecture) as the method involves communication between edge devices and the server.
